Package fi.tuni.tamk.objectOrientedProgramming

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    MyJsonArray
    Represents a JSON array surrounded by square brackets [].
    MyJsonElement
    This Abstract class holds the method necessary for all element classes.
    MyJsonNull
    An object of this class is simply a null value for easier printing.
    MyJsonObject
    Represents a JSON object surrounded by curly brackets {}.
    MyJsonParser
    Converts JSON values from a String into Java Objects.
    MyJsonPrimitive
    A JSON primitive represents a String, Number or Boolean value.
    MyJsonReader
    Reads the file in a received path and returns it as a one-line String.
    MyJsonValue Deprecated.
    MyJsonValuePair
    A JSON value pair holds a key and a value assigned to that key.
    MyJsonWriter
    Used in order to track white space usage when writing in JSON format.
